A man convicted of imprisoning a 9-year-old girl for 17 days in a suburban New York dungeon has been found dead in his prison cell.

A state corrections spokeswoman said John Esposito, 64, was found unresponsive in his cell at Sing Sing Wednesday. She said the death was under investigation but didn't appear to be suspicious.

He was serving a 15-to-life term for kidnapping Katie Beers and hiding her for 17 days under his Bay Shore, New York, home in 1992.

