Linda Foglia said a corrections officer observed Esposito ‘not breathing’ around 3.30pm at the Ossining, New York, correctional facility.

Officials said they believe the 64-year-old inmate died of natural causes. 

According to Beers, her tormentor was found dead in his cell after appearing before a parole board to find out if he would be released after serving 20 years in prison, News 12 Long Island reported.

Miss Beers said in a statement to CBS-TV she is saddened at the loss of a life, but at the same time happy Esposito will ‘never be granted parole or have the opportunity to hurt anyone ever again.’

The survivor of the kidnapping also took to Twitter to share her thoughts on the passing of her abductor. 

